    <stitle>ELECTRICAL SYSTEM TROUBLESHOOTING GUIDE - 9800 - SINGLE REDUCTION, SINGLE DRIVE AXLES: EATON - DISASSEMBLE
    </stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcsubsec>
        <title>DISASSEMBLE</title>
        <svcproc svcproctype="disassemble" graphiccount="5">
            <title>DRIVE PINION</title>
            <specpara>
                <caution>
                    <para>During the following yoke removal procedure, do not allow pinion to drop on the hard
                        surface.
                    </para>
                </caution>
            </specpara>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">If pinion nut was not loosened during earlier disassembly, clamp yoke in vise jaws. Use
                    brass pads to prevent damage. Loosen and remove pinion nut. To remove yoke, use suitable puller or
                    press pinion out of yoke.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Support cage and press pinion out of bearing cage (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1401210">Figure 10</hotlnk>).
                </para>
                <figure id="f1401210" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="g1401210" filename="../figg14/g1401210.webp" type="webp" resolution="72"/>
                    <caption>Figure 10. Remove Drive Pinion</caption>
                </figure>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Press oil seal and outer bearing cup out of cage (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1401211">Figure 11</hotlnk>). Discard oil seal. On axles 23105 through 30105,
                    remove and discard O-ring.
                </para>
                <figure id="f1401211" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="g1401211" filename="../figg14/g1401211.webp" type="webp" resolution="72"/>
                    <caption>Figure 11. Press Oil Seal and Outer Bearing Cup Out of Cage</caption>
                </figure>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove and retain bearing spacer from pinion.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Using a suitable bearing cup remover, remove inner bearing cup (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1401212">Figure 12</hotlnk>).
                </para>
                <figure id="f1401212" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="g1401212" filename="../figg14/g1401212.webp" type="webp"/>
                    <caption>Figure 12. Remove Inner Bearing Cup</caption>
                </figure>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove pilot bearing and inner bearing cone from pinion, using a split-type puller. Use
                    two procedure steps to remove each bearing.
                </para>
                <step2>
                    <para count="1">FIRST, mount splitter vertically to split bearing (
                        <hotlnk xrefid="f1401213">Figure 13</hotlnk>).
                    </para>
                    <figure id="f1401213" figsize="col-wide">
                        <graphic id="g1401213" filename="../figg14/g1401213.webp" type="webp"/>
                        <caption>Figure 13. Mount Splitter Vertically to Split Bearing</caption>
                    </figure>
                </step2>
                <step2>
                    <para count="1">SECOND, mount splitter horizontally to remove bearing (
                        <hotlnk xrefid="f1401214">Figure 14</hotlnk>).
                    </para>
                    <figure id="f1401214" figsize="col-wide">
                        <graphic id="g1401214" filename="../figg14/g1401214.webp" type="webp" resolution="72"/>
                        <caption>Figure 14. Mount Splitter Horizontally to Remove Bearing</caption>
                    </figure>
                </step2>
            </step1>
        </svcproc>
    </svcsubsec>
